Declare and initialize a character array of size 50 with any character sequence.
Implement a linear search procedure to find a character entered by the user in this array.

The return value of the search function is 0 if the searched character is not present in the array, otherwise, it is the index of the searched character.

Use the provided code skeleton, and ensure that the return type, function name (identifier), and parameter list of the functions adhere to the given requirements.

The test.c file contains CUnit tests:
Tested function Parameter Expected return value
search 'd', "abc" 4
search 'z', "abc" 26
search '5', "abc" 0
